cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with normalization layers in deep neural networks for vision applications, specifically object detection, semantic segmentation, and instance segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new normalization layer, which involves algorithmic solutions, indicating a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions performance and transfer learning, which suggests a focus on optimization and neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with benchmark datasets, indicating a focus on multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
